HEADWORD: Heresiarchy
<hw>Her"e*si*arch`y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A chief or
great heresy.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The book itself [the Alcoran] consists of <qex>heresiarchies</qex>
against our blessed Savior.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heresiographer</ent>⟦br⟧
